issue.title: _.delete/_.remove for objects using a path.
issue.body:
It would be great to be able to remove a value from an object, including it's key using a path just like `_.get` and `_.set`.

```javascript
_.remove(object, 'a[0].b.c');
```

issue.title: _.branch: _.pick and _.omit simultaneously

comment.body:
I propose that  _.branch could accept a collection of functions and return an array containing collections of elements. Each of the functions would decide whether to add the iterated element to the corresponding collection. 

The functions could be passed an extra boolean informing whether the iterated element has already been picked by one of the previous functions. This way we would optionally be able to add the unmatched elements to the last collection.

npm no longer contains lodash.min.js
issue.body:
I'm using npm as my front end package manager, and have been using the /dist/lodash.min.js file for a long time.

Is it a bug or a feature? :P

comment.body:
> With the simplicity of minifiers these days I've put more time into my reply then it would take you to minify or bundle your third-party deps appropriately

This is unnecessarily condescending.

The fact remains that @leon has use case that, while you may not encourage, is nevertheless valid.  I would argue that there is a legit concern tied to minifying code you don't own.  Unless you are going to stop publishing the minified uber-build, it seems silly to stop including in the npm distro.
